	  <title>Examples of Preimage of a Function</title>
	  <caption>Preimage of a Function</caption>
	  <example>
		    <statement.example>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Find the preimage of <math>
                  <latex>y\in \RNr</latex>
               </math> of the function</para.body>
         </para>
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>f\from \RNr[2] \longrightarrow \RNr,\qquad f(u,v) = u^2 +v^2</latex>
			      </math.display>
		    </statement.example>
		
		    <answer type="Solution" version="1">
         <answer.block>
            <answer.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>In this case we can use geometric reasoning to answer this problem: <math>
                        <latex>f</latex>
                     </math> sends a point <math>
                        <latex>(u,v)</latex>
                     </math> to the number <math>
                        <latex>u^2+v^2</latex>
                     </math>. This is the square of the distance of <math>
                        <latex>(u,v)</latex>
                     </math> from the origin. Therefore</para.body>
               </para>
			
			            <ul>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The preimage of <math>
                              <latex>y=0</latex>
                           </math> in <math>
                              <latex>\RNr</latex>
                           </math> is the origin <math>
                              <latex>(0,0)</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The preimage of <math>
                              <latex> y&gt;0 </latex>
                           </math> in <math>
                              <latex>\RNr</latex>
                           </math> is the circle in <math>
                              <latex>\RNr[2]</latex>
                           </math> centered at <math>
                              <latex>(0,0)</latex>
                           </math> of radius <math>
                              <latex>\sqrt{y}</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The preimage of <math>
                              <latex> y&lt; 0 </latex>
                           </math> is empty; i.e. the equation <math>
                              <latex>f(u,v)=y</latex>
                           </math> has no solution if <math>
                              <latex> y&lt;0 </latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
			            </ul>
			
