	  <example>
		    <statement.example>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Find the preimage of the number <math>
                  <latex>k</latex>
               </math> under the function </para.body>
         </para>
			
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>f\from \RNr[2] \longrightarrow \RNr,\qquad f(x,y) = 2x + y</latex>
			      </math.display>
		    </statement.example>
		
		    <answer type="Solution" version="1">
         <answer.block>
            <answer.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>We need to solve the equation <math>
                        <latex>2x+y = k</latex>
                     </math>. This equation is linear. So we know that the solutions form a line in <math>
                        <latex>\RNr[2]</latex>
                     </math>, which is perpendicular to the vector <math>
                        <latex>\Vect{n} = (2,1)</latex>
                     </math>.</para.body>
               </para>
			
			            <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
                  <img src="ims/FunctionPreimage_Linear.gif"/>
               </media>
			
			            <para>
                  <para.body>Thus we see that the preimage of a colored dot on the right is the line of the same color on the left. This implies that the function    transforms each of the colored lines on the left into the single point of the same color on the right.</para.body>
               </para>
		          </answer.block.body>
         </answer.block>
      </answer>
	  </example>
	
